        "order": 7
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_PPT_ch7_page_057_7",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "If this is the only m-tuple of scalars for which (1) holds, then our vectors a1), ..., a(m) are said to form a linearly independent set or, more briefly, we call them linearly independent.",
